46:35.457 --> 46:36.678
sense. Why six weeks? Why can't you make it on a 
system of week by week? And working with a student

46:42.163 --> 46:47.829
to progress and helping them succeed. Not use it as 
punishment. Use it as a means of motivation and

46:50.091 --> 46:55.476
incentive But somebody's got to work with the 
student. It doesn't do any good to just say you

47:00.141 --> 47:04.386
can't participate for six weeks. Somebody ought 
to be working with that student before they get to

47:05.327 --> 47:11.615
the situation where they don't pass. And then if 
they don't pass, somebody ought to be working with

47:12.195 --> 47:15.119
them right off. And there ought to be some 
incentives, some goal set. And then if the student

47:19.885 --> 47:24.450
meets those goals, then you Move ahead and help you 
feel like a success if you don't do things in terms

47:25.443 --> 47:31.672
of six-week chunks. People who are 15 and 16 don't 
live their lives that way. They don't think of

47:36.438 --> 47:37.980
those things. We're going to lose a lot of kids from 
school. The thing I'm hoping that somebody does is

47:41.986 --> 47:50.758
hold each of these school districts to the 
requirement in the legislation that they do.

